result.name: Ajisen Ramen

reviews.text:
Good location and spacious before you go to Macau by ferry.
Food is really average, but you can't really ask for too much.
Returning from Macao, my wife and I came here for lunch. Food and service are very good. They do not charge service charge!
Good food for low prices. The waiters speak little to no english, but the menu is in english and you can just point.

I haven't had a meal in an Ajisen Ramen restaurant for years, but my daughter chose it because she was in the mood for ramen. It has almost empty, which was a positive, but the meal was below average for price. I wouldn't go back.

The view of people earing ramen here made us want to eat here right off the long trip from Macau.

Customer service is good and the food was good as well. It was even better for me because i was starving and finished the spicy beef ramen in less than 10 minutes.
